        <headline>Cold Weather Advisory issued November 30 at 1:56AM MST until December 1 at 10:00AM MST by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>* WHAT...For the Freezing Fog Advisory, visibility less than one
mile in freezing fog. For the Cold Weather Advisory, very cold
wind chills as low as 35 below.

* WHERE...Hill County.

* WHEN...For the Freezing Fog Advisory, until 9 AM MST this morning.
For the Cold Weather Advisory, until 10 AM MST Monday.

* IMPACTS...The dangerously cold wind chills as low as 35 below zero
could cause frostbite on exposed skin in as little as 10 minutes.
Low visibility could make driving conditions hazardous.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...A light glaze of ice from the freezing fog
will make for slick travel this morning.
</description>
        <instruction>Use caution while traveling outside. Wear appropriate clothing, a
hat, and gloves.

If driving, slow down, use your headlights, and leave plenty of
distance ahead of you.</instruction>
